      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E, nu) sourced from ASTM-certified coupon testing of production-lot titanium alloy. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of production implants. Uncertainty in elastic modulus (±3 GPa) propagated via sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 production implants from two independent manufacturing lots tested across two laboratories. Sample traceability documented; implant geometry confirmed via CMM prior to testing. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison at the declared model risk level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load angle (5 degrees) per ASTM F1717 protocol. Multi-angle loading not evaluated; this constitutes a known gap reducing achieved level to 2 against required level 3. Accepted on basis of regulatory precedent for F1717 single-condition submissions."
    },
    {
