      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Primary QOI is construct stiffness (N/mm) under compression-bending, directly linked to the regulatory submission metric. Secondary QOI peak pedicle screw bending moment also extracted and compared. Both QOIs are clinically and regulatorily meaningful for spinal fixation device assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities replicate the exact ASTM F1717 bench test configuration referenced in the regulatory submission. Device geometry, material, and loading protocol in validation are identical to those in the intended regulatory use scenario. Relevance gap limited to single-angle test condition limitation captured under Test conditions factor."
    }
