    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for model risk level 3. The single deficient factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis of regulatory precedent for ASTM F1717 single-condition bench submissions and is documented as a known scope limitation within the claim and requirement narrative. Overall evidence package supports medium assurance level for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending FEA model in the context of Class II pre-market submission under 21 CFR 888.3070.",
